Hoeffding multiplier comparison: 2|Gamma| (one-sided) vs 4|Gamma| (two-sided)
==============================================================================
  Purpose: quantify the tail difference to justify the recommended choice.

  n=  250 | t(2|Gamma|)=0.115625 | t(4|Gamma|)=0.121472 | gap=0.005847 (4.81% relative)
  n=  500 | t(2|Gamma|)=0.081759 | t(4|Gamma|)=0.085894 | gap=0.004134 (4.81% relative)
  n= 1000 | t(2|Gamma|)=0.057813 | t(4|Gamma|)=0.060736 | gap=0.002923 (4.81% relative)
  n= 2000 | t(2|Gamma|)=0.040880 | t(4|Gamma|)=0.042947 | gap=0.002067 (4.81% relative)
  n= 5000 | t(2|Gamma|)=0.025855 | t(4|Gamma|)=0.027162 | gap=0.001307 (4.81% relative)

