==============================================================================
Summary
==============================================================================
  * Theorem 1 directional bound: computed rho_+/rho_- match hand calc.
  * Theorem 3 finite-sample tail: computed t matches hand calc (~0.082).
  * Certificate non-vacuous on the baseline toy config for R_hat up to
    approximately 0.418 (i.e., 0.5 - t).
  * 2|Gamma| vs 4|Gamma| gap grows slowly; see the multiplier comparison
    section for exact numbers at various n.
  * Skeleton Section 7 Self-Review Checklist item 9 (non-vacuous
    numerical example) is now supported by this deterministic script.
